      "text": [
        " عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ: «إِذَا نَزَلَتْ بِالرَّجُلِ اَلنَّازِلَةُ أَوِ اَلشِّدَّةُ فَلْيَصُمْ فَإِنَّ اَللَّهَ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ يَقُولُ:\n«۝ وَ اِسْتَعِينُوا بِالصَّبْرِ وَ اَلصَّلاٰةِ ۝» »"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1777 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said:\n\"If a person faces a calamity or hardship, let him fast, for Allah (swt), the Almighty, says: \"And seek help through patience and prayer\" (Surah Al-Baqarah 2:45)"
        ]
      }
    },
